definition.value: A  myo-inositol cyclic phosphate that is the 1,2-cyclic phosphate derivative of 1D-myo-inositol.
A member of the class of methyl myo-inositols that is cyclohexane-1,2,3,4,5-pentol substituted by a methoxy group at position 6 (the 1R,2R,3S,4S,5R,6S-isomer).
A fenchane monoterpenoid that is substituted by methyl groups at positions 3, 5, and 5, and by both a hydroxy group and a 3-oxobut-1-en-1-yl group at position 4.
An EC 2.3.2.* (aminoacyltransferase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of beta-N-acetylhexosaminidase (EC 2.3.2.52).
An acyl chloride consisting of benzoyl chloride in which the hydrogen at position 4 is replaced by a cyano group.
An aminoxyl that is N-tert-butyl-2-methylpropan-2-amine carrying an oxidanediyl group at the nitrogen atom.
A member of the class of oxazolidines that is 4,4-dimethyl-1,3-oxazolidine carrying an oxidanediyl group at position 3.
